                            <comment id="53978" author="fenrir" created="Fri, 21 May 2010 02:39:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like the description of the issue I submitted doesn&apos;t appear. So I rewrite the description in this comment:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If my application is located at: &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8080/myapp*&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8080/myapp*&lt;/a&gt; and I want to include the context root in a logical view name, I have to type the name like this: *redirect:/myapp/secure/user/info&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be nice if we can use a shortcut like: *redirect:$&lt;/p&gt;
{base}
&lt;p&gt;/secure/user/info*&lt;/p&gt;




